HEADWORD: bushwhack
<hw>bush"whack`</hw> <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>to lie in ambush for, lie in
wait for.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> ambush, scupper, lie for, waylay, lurk,
ambuscade.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>bushwhack</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: bushwhack
<hw>bush"whack`</hw> <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>to live in the
bush as a fugitive or as a guerilla.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>to cut one's way through the woods or
bush.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bushwhacker</ent>⟦br⟧
